Hundreds of households, businessmen, traders and artisans are protesting prolonged and epileptic power supply at Jega local government area of Kebbi state. Speaking to newsmen at his workshop in Jega town, the branch chairman of welders association Malam Samaila Haruna said that power supply is completely not there as throughout the day they get power for just one hour or even less and most times they restore power around 5 pm when they have wind up the business using generators. According to him before the new manager was deployed to Jega power supply was steady but since the new one assumed office he messed up things and has been forcing them to pay for darkness “look at my service wire they have disconnected it since January the 16th 2020 and iam not bothered because iam using generators to do my welding works which i even found better, KEDCO had forced many of my former boys out of welding business because they cannot afford generators.” ASUU  Strike Grounds Academic Activities At FUBK In Kebbi Alleged Ineptitude: Angry Onicha-Ugbo Youths Protest Against… Another artisan a carpenter who doubles as the treasurer of carpenters association Jega branch Musa Shehu lamented that his business has completely stopped due to poor or no power supply, according to him almost 50 apprentices works under him but only one is around because there is no electricity to cut woods and other works that requires power to do “I am appealing to KEDCO and the state government to wade in to save my business from collapsing as we are losing thousands due to poor supply, asides protest he said they will not hesitate to deploy other means to get their demands met if nothing concrete is done. Sufiyanu Tanko Jega a businessman and a household said that the epileptic supply affected him as thieves took advantage of the darkness to burgle his shop and made away with huge cash a week-long sales, he noted that apart from the loss of perishable items darkness has aggravated the security situation of the town warning that if nothing is done to salvage their situation it will affect the governor politically because the people of Jega town are not happy with what is happening in Jega. Honourable Murtala Habibu Musa Jega the executive chairman of Jega Local Government in his reaction to the unfortunate development said that he assumed duties last two weeks but have been under pressure over the issue “I have set up a committee to look into it and find a lasting solution to the power challenge, I met with the officials of Kaduna electricity distribution company and they gave me their words that the supply will improve, he urged the people of Jega to be calm as something is being done.In his reaction to the demands of the protesters the head of communication Kebbi district office of KEDCO Malam Najib appeal to Jega consumers to exercise restraint as efforts are being made to ensure steady power supply to Jega town as soon as few issues are resolved “we regret loses and inconveniences caused, we resolved to satisfy our customer remains intact. He added that when load allocation improves from the transmission company of Nigeria supply will improve saying the problem didn’t emanate from them as the distribution company.